@graph.schema:description:
This supplementary resource provides a list and details of priority links (road segments) that appear in the below dataset resources. 

Links can be thought of as the segment of road from Node A > Node B. Each road segment contains an origin node (start) and a destination node (finish) to indicate the direction of travel.

For example, the origin node – "1181" – refers to the "Intersection of Gympie Road and Todds Road (M2145)", whilst the destination node – "1515" – refers to "Intersection of Anzac Avenue and Station Street (M2158)".  Combined, the two form a node-to-node road segment that is written as 1181->1515.
@graph.schema:name: Priority Route Link Details
